fo","properties":{},"widgets_values":["🔧 Tiled Diffusion – Key Parameters\n\n| Parameter         | Description                                                                 |\n|-------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| `tile_size`       | Width & height of each tile. Recommended: 512, 768, 1024.                   |\n|                   | 🔹 512 – safest, low VRAM                                                    |\n|                   | 🔹 768 – fast, stable, great for portraits                                   |\n|                   | 🔹 1024 – high detail, but can add \"extra stuff\" & takes longer              |\n| `tile_overlap`    | Pixels shared between tiles. Prevents seams. Use 32–128 based on tile size. |\n|                   | 🔹 32 for 512 tiles, 64 for 768, 128 for 1024                                |\n| `tile_batch_size` | Tiles processed at once. Higher = faster, but uses more VRAM.               |\n|                   | 🔹 1–2 = safe and clean                                                      |\n|                   | 🔹 4–6 = fast on 24GB GPUs (like RTX 4090)                                   |\n\n💡 Tips:\n- Use **square tiles** (width = height)\n- Match **overlap** to tile size to avoid seams\n- 768 is often the sweet spot for quality + speed\n- 1024 tiles may generate more detail, but also more \"creative noise\"\n"],"color":"#323","bgcolor":"#535"},{"id":232,"type":"VAEDecode","pos":[1070.5987548828125,201.1582794189453],"size":[225,72],"flags":{"collapsed":false},"order":21,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"localized_name":"samples","name":"samples","type":"LATENT","link":265},{"localized_name":"vae","name":"vae","type":"VAE","link":266}],"outputs":[{"localized_name":"IMAGE","name":"IMAGE","type":"IMAGE","slot_index":0,"links":[269,272,282]}],"properties":{"cnr_id":"comfy-core","ver":"0.3.27","Node name for S&R":"VAEDecode"},"widgets_values":[]},{"id":250,"type":"easy imageScaleDownToSize","pos":[-4